                <head>Execution of the Laws</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Complaint about the quality of justice being meted out in VA, specifically
                    its lenience, and the tendency for public sentiment to extend to criminals, not
                    their victims. Calls for a more rigid enforcement of the laws, and mandatory
                    hanging for murder.</summary>
