            <div type="a">
                <column>4</column>
                <head>The Next Legislature</head>
                <origin>Lynchburg Virginian</origin>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>What right have such men as these to be in private life, while the grave
                    affairs of the Commonwealth are committed to inexperienced or feeble hands?</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>Lynchburg Virginian</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>Endorses plan of Albemarle County citizens to elect local notables and then
                    compell them to serve. Should be extended to all counties. Men shouldn't be able
                    to turn down service to their state</summary>
            </div>
